	title	'Run-time BOOT/SYS patches for XLR8er-patched systems'	header	'Functional description & equates'	print	short,nomacourbase:equ	7a00h			;Below 32K and well out of the way.	psect	ourbase;----------------------------------------------------------------------------;	XLR8SET by M. A. D. Software.  Copyright 1990, All Rights Reserved.;	Some of the patches that this program applies were published;	by MISOSYS, Inc.;	The purchaser may not transfer or provide copies of the binary,;	object, executable or source of this program to any third party;	without prior written permission from M. A. D.  Software.;	The purchaser may make any modifications to the source that are;	required to customize this software to his/her personal systems.;	If modified, M. A. D. may decline to support the entire program.;	The HOUDE patches HA-HM (as published by MISOSYS) are provided;	"AS IS" and are not supported by M. A. D. Software in any way.;<2>	The M. A. D. Software substitution patches are also provided "AS IS";<2>	and are Copyright 1990, M. A. D.  Software, All Rights Reserved.;<2>	These patches may not be transferred in any form to any other system.;								002117;----------------------------------------------------------------------------;  OVERVIEW:;	This program will apply the "patches" to RAM that would normally be;	permanently applied to BOOT/SYS and SYS0/SYS.;	The problem is that although the low-core area has enough space for;	several small drivers, only a portion of this RAM can be loaded at;	boot time as part of BOOT/SYS.;	If hard disk boot capability was desired, the hard disk driver MUST;	be present in BOOT/SYS to allow the boot to complete.  This driver;	must start immediately after the floppy driver, otherwise it will not;	be in the section of RAM that is loaded by the boot ROM and bootstrap.;	The HOUDE XLR8er patches ALSO want to be placed immediately after the;	the floppy disk driver for the same reason.  However, these patches;	are not necessary until after the DATE/TIME prompting is performed.;	Even if either the hard disk driver or the patches are relocated,;	there is insufficent room in BOOT/SYS to permanently store both.;	Therefore, this program should be run as the AUTO command or one of;	the first commands in the JCL log (before any attempts are made to;	access the extra RAM of the XLR8er adapter.); ***	This program will apply ALL patches that are needed by BOOT/SYS AND; ***	SYS0/SYS.  THESE PATCHES MUST NOT BE PRESENT IN THE SYS0/SYS AND; ***	BOOT/SYS FILES IF HARD DISK BOOTING IS TO BE PERFORMED.  XLR8SET ; ***	Finds the next available location in RAM for certain patches and; ***	updates all references to the relocated area.  (Hard Disk boot users; ***	MUST complete the entire installation of the hsrd disk boot system; ***	before running XLR8SET.);	Continued on next page	eject;	The usage line for this program is:;		XLR8SET [-q] [-s] [-m [-b "progname"]] [progname....];	-q causes XLR8SET to run silently with no messages being displayed;		if everything works like it should.;	-s causes XLR8SET to not change the speed settings of the 64180.;		All other 64180 initialization is performed.;	-b causes XLR8SET to execute the immediately following command;		(or commands) PRIOR to performing its other functions.;		This can be used to load the clock or perform other;		operations that require a CPU speed closer to that of a normal;		Model 4/4D/4P.;		Nested quotes are not allowed, so #, $, %, & and ' can;		also be used in place of the quotes.;		Example:   -b 'prog1 ....' prog2;		will cause prog1 to execute before XLR8SET runs and prog2;		will be run after XLR8SET completes.;<3>		NOTE:	prog1 must not overwrite or otherwise clear the;<3>			RAM where XLR8SET resides.  XLR8SET will set HIGH$ to;<3>			protect itself but this will not stop program loads.;<3>			(See the -m option for control of HIGH$.);<3>	-m prevents XLR8SET from adjusting the location of HIGH$ while;<3>		processing -b commands.  If drivers or other high memory;<3>		modules are to be installed via -b commands, -m will;<3>		leave HIGH$ undisturbed.;<3>		NOTE:	When -m is used, it must appear in front of all;<3>			of the -b option(s) on the command line.;	The various switches may be used together.  The -b option may be;	used more than once if more than one command is to be performed;	prior to XLR8er initialization.  For Example:;		XLR8SET -b "date" -q -b "time" dir;	will display the date and time, initialize the hardware, then;	display the directory.;	progname.....  will be executed as though it was the only command in;	the AUTO command buffer or on the command line.  The combination of;	this and the -q should make the presence of XLR8SET invisible. If;	XLR8SET runs into problems, the additional commands (progname) will;	not be executed and an error message is displayed..;<3>	The program is currently configured for LS-DOS 6.3.0 and 6.3.1 and;<3>	will refuse to run on other versions.  Using it on operating systems;<3>	or other versions without verifying the patches may cause problems.;	NOTE: THIS PROGRAM DOES NOT VERIFY THE CORRECTNESS OF THE PATCHES OR;	      ADDRESSES GIVEN, NOR DOES IT MATCH AGAINST THE EXISTING CONTENTS;	      OF THE SPECIFIED ADDRESSES.  IT DOES FOLLOW ALL CONVENTIONS OF;	      LOW AND HIGH MEMORY DRIVER ALLOCATION AND INSTALLATION.	eject;	Edit	History EDIT edit VERSION version Version HISTORY history;	Edit	1	Initial version.;			December 1989  M. A. D. Software;	Edit	2	Upgraded to layer in our own D2, F2 and H2 patches.;			The original HD, HF and HH HOUDE patches are available;			via conditional assembly.  The HOUSE low-core @BANK;			svc/driver requires about 127 bytes.  The compatible;			version of these patches uses less than 35 bytes of;			low-core driver space.;			Setup code was added to transfer any existing bank;			assignment to the new Bank Access Word BAW.;			Standardized relative/absolute/offset address;			computation.;			Added -s and -b options. See overview for usage.;			10-Feb-90  M. A. D. Software;	Edit	3	Verification of support with LS-DOS 6.3.1.;			Added code to lock out patching on versions other than;			LS-DOS 6.3.0 and 6.3.1.;			Tightened low-core driver.  Banks 1 and 2 are now;			assigned the same numbers as LS-DOS has always;			assigned them.  This was done to prevent programs that;			run the hardware themselves from messing things up.;			Move HIGH$ down below XLR8SET while it is running.;			22-Mar-90  M. A. D. Software;	Edit	4	Cleanup of source for distribution.   NO CODE CHANGES.;			1-Jul-90  M. A. D.  Software;	Edit	5	Merged in modern command line parser.;			27-Jul-93  M. A. D. Software;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------VERSION:defm	'XLR8SET - XLR8er patch loader for BOOT & SYS0 - '	defm	'Version   1(5) 27-Jul-93   '	;<3>	defb	0ah	defm	'Copyright 1990, 1993, M. A. D. Software.  '	defm	'All Rights Reserved.'	defb	0ah,0dh	eject;	O P T I O N S;----------------------------------------Options for assembly & 64180 init.newpatch:equ	1			;1==New @BANK SVC and overflow driver					;0==Original HOUDE patch HD, HF & HHmaxbanks:equ	10			;Maximum number of banks newpatch					;will allow.waits:	equ	40h			;Value to write to DMA/WAIT Control					;Register in 64180refresh:equ	02h			;Refresh setting for REFRESH register;----------------------------------------	ejectosmajor:equ	063h			;LS-DOS 6.3.xosminorl:equ	020h			;LS-DOS x.x.1 or x.x.0@cmndi:	equ	24			;Issue a command@cmndr:	equ	25			;Issue a command and come back@abort:	equ	21			;Abort execution@dsp:	equ	2			;Display a single character@dsply:	equ	10			;Display a string@flags:	equ	101			;<3>Flags@gtmod:	equ	83			;Locate existing modules@high:	equ	100			;<3>High$@exit:	equ	22			;ExitBUR$:	equ	0200h			;<2>Bank Use Register (normal LS-DOS)BAR$:	equ	0201h			;<2>Bank Available Register (n LS-DOS)LBANK$:	equ	0202h			;Last bank access in binaryDVRHI$:	equ	0206h			;<2>Start of [unused] low I/O zoneLPERR:	equ	0dedh			;Loaded 2B in A, sets NZ and returnsOPREG$:	equ	0078h			;RAM-image of write-only command portCBR:	equ	38h			;CBR port in 64180  (R/W)OPREGR:	equ	84h			;OPREG command port (W)ldos	macro	#1	ld	a,#1	rst	28h	endmin0	macro	#1,#2			;Emulate IN0	A,(n)	defb	0edh,038h,#2	endmout0	macro	#1,#2			;Emulate OUT0	(n),A	defb	0edh,039h,#1	endm	header	'Read and process command-line options'begin:	ld	de,ourbuf			ld	bc,82	ldir;	Now we start processing the command line.  Each time we find a;	devicespec or modulename we place it in the pattern buffer and;	attempt to display those devices.  	ld	hl,ourbuf		;<2>Use our buf from now onparnew:	xor	a			;Contains defaults and command line	ld	(inoption),a		;Reset option flagparnxt:	ld	a,(hl)			;Pick up character	cp	' '			;Space?	jr	nz,parnsp		;No	xor	a	ld	(inoption),a		;Not an option anymoreparadv:	inc	hl	jr	parnxt			;Skipparnsp:	cp	'-'			;Option switch	jr	z,paropt		;Handle option	cp	0dh			;End?	jp	z,parend		;End of parms to parse	ld	b,a			;Save character	ld	a,(inoption)		;Did we process an option last?	or	a	ld	a,b			;Get back original character	jp	nz,opt2			;Possibly a -abc option format	cp	';'	jp	nz,badopt	inc	hl	call	skipspa	cp	0dh	jp	z,parend	ld	(nxtcmd),hl		;Store trailing command position	jp	parend			;End of parms to parseskipspa:ld	a,(hl)	cp	' '	ret	nz	inc	hl	jr	skipspa	eject;	Parse option switches and parametersparopt:	inc	hl			;Bump past '-'	ld	a,(hl)			;Get option code	ld	(inoption),a		;Remember we were hereopt2:	or	20h			;Fold case	cp	's'			;Speed control	jr	z,gos	cp	'b'	jr	z,gob	cp	'm'	jr	z,gom	cp	'q'	jr	nz,badoptgoq:	ld	(quiet),a		;Set non-zero	jr	paradv			;<2>gos:	ld	(slow),a	jr	paradv			;<2>gom:	ld	(lockmem),a		;<3>Set NZ	jr	paradvgob:	inc	hl			;<2>	ld	a,(hl)			;<2>	cp	' '			;<2>	jr	z,gob			;<2>	cp	0dh			;<2>	jp	z,parend		;<2>False alarm	cp	'('			;<2>Allow several delims	jr	c,stx			;<2>Any will do	jp	badopt			;<2>Huh?stx:	ld	b,a			;<2>Save delimeter	inc	hl			;<2>	push	hl			;<2>stxr:	ld	a,(hl)			;<2>	cp	b			;<2>Look for match	jr	z,etx			;<2>	cp	0dh			;<2>	jp	z,badopt		;<2>	inc	hl			;<2>	jr	stxr			;<2>	ejectetx:	push	hl			;<3>	ld	a,(lockmem)		;<3>Have we forbid moving high?	or	a			;<3>	jr	nz,nomov1		;<3>Skip this	ld	hl,(oldhigh)		;<3>Have we done this already?	ld	a,h			;<3>	or	l			;<3>	jr	nz,nomov1		;<3>Skip this	ld	hl,0			;<3>	ld	b,0			;<3>	ldos	@high			;<3>Read current high$ value	ld	(oldhigh),hl		;<3>Save HL	ld	hl,ourbase		;<3>Our base	dec	hl			;<3>	dec	hl			;<3>	ldos	@high			;<3>Set our HLnomov1:	pop	hl			;<3>	ld	(hl),0dh		;<2>Terminate string	ex	(sp),hl			;<2>Get base back	ldos	@cmndr			;<2>Execute command now	pop	hl			;<2>Get back addr	inc	hl			;<5>	jp	parnew			;<2>Jump back into commonbadopt:	ld	hl,VERSION	ldos	@dsply	ld	hl,USAGE	ldos	@dsply	ld	hl,0	ldos	@exit	header	'Test the system and load the patches';	Does the target have a Hitachi 64180parend:	xor	a	scf	defb	0edh,03ch		;TST A opcode - this sequence is a NOP	ld	hl,BAD4MSG		;on a plain Z80.  64180 clears carry.	jp	c,ab1	ld	a,(BAR$)		;<2>Get status of lower RAM	cp	0f8h			;<2>All 128K there?	ld	hl,BAD5MSG		;<2>Don't let them run if not	jp	nz,ab1			;<2>Abort if base system is 64K;	Make sure the system version is what we expect.	ldos	@flags			;<3>Get flags	ld	hl,BAD8MSG		;<3>Error message to use	ld	a,(iy+27)		;<3>Version ID byte 	cp	osmajor			;<3>LS-DOS 6.3 OPERATING SYSTEM	jp	nz,ab1			;<3>Abort if no match	ld	a,(iy-47)		;<3>Get LSB	and	0f0h			;<3>Check range	cp	osminorl		;<3>limit of range	jp	nc,ab1			;<3>Out of range	eject;	Test to see if the driver is already present	ld	de,tmpname		;Point at temp area	ld	b,0	ld	hl,a_modname		;Get length of module name	ld	c,(hl)	inc	hl			;Advance to string	ldir				;Copy it	xor	a	ld	(de),a			;Terminate it	ld	de,tmpname		;Point at copy	ldos	@gtmod			;loaded.  If so, must not add again	ld	hl,BAD3MSG	jp	z,ab1			;Abort - driver already loaded	ld	hl,12ffh		;See if it will fit	ld	de,(DVRHI$)		;<2>Get first free location	ld	(daddr),de	or	a	sbc	hl,de			;Well?	jp	c,bad1			;We are negative already;	HL now has the amount of free space left	ld	de,DRVSIZ		;Get size of driver (patch)	or	a	sbc	hl,de			;Will it fit?	jp	c,bad2			;<2>Nope	eject;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------;	At this point the overflow, located in a fake driver, will be able;	to fit in low core and we have a base address.;	This code modifies the patches that refer to that driver;	(HA, HD, D2, HE, HH, and H2) to reflect the current address.;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------	ex	de,hl			;Size of driver in HL	ld	de,(DVRHI$)		;<2>Get base address	add	hl,de			;New free base address	ld	(a_newfre),hl		;Update that  - PATCH HA	dec	hl			;Point at last free byte	ld	(a_endmod),hl		;Store that piece of information					;in "driver"	ld	hl,o_bentry		;Get offset into driver	add	hl,de	ld	(a_baddr),hl		;Update Bank code addr - PATCH HD/D2	ld	hl,o_ventry		;Get offset again	add	hl,de	ld	(a_vaddr),hl		;Update vdctl address - PATCH HE	ift	newpatch	ld	a,(BUR$)		;<2>Get current RAM status	and	7			;<2>	ld	(a_baw),a		;<2>Store info in Bank Access Word	endif;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------;	This section of code applies all patches as they now match the;	local configuration.;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------	di	;-------------------------------------------------------------	ld	hl,opatches		;Get the patch addressmore:	ld	e,(hl)			;Read address LSB	inc	hl	ld	d,(hl)			;MSB	inc	hl	ld	a,d			;If address is zero, all done	or	e	jr	z,done	ld	c,(hl)			;Read length	ld	b,0	inc	hl	ldir				;Copy to target	jr	more	eject;----------------------------------------------------------------------------;	All patches in table have been applied.;	Now initialize the hardware (this would have been done in the boot;	steps of SYS0/SYS and that region has already run.;	The settings used in this section are the same as those made;	by the MISOSYS patches.   THE VARIOUS SETTINGS ARE PROVIDED "AS IS".;----------------------------------------------------------------------------done:	ld	a,(slow)		;<2>	or	a	jr	nz,skipspd		;<2>Don't change speed settings	ld	a,waits			;7 = 0  MWI1 - original value 0x40					;6 = 1	MWI0					;5 = 0	IOW1					;4 = 0	IOW0					;3 = 0	DMS1					;2 = 0	DMS0					;1 = 0	DIM1					;0 = 0	DIM0	out0	(32h),a			;DMA/WAIT Control Register	in0	a,(36h)			;Refresh Control Register	and	0fch			;Clear Cycle Interval					;Refresh still enabled					;Refresh 3 clocks long	or	refresh			;Set Bit 1 = 40 states ~ 6.6 usec					;Original value 0x02	out0	(36h),a			;Refresh Control Registerskipspd:				;<2>	xor	a			;For next outs (A15-A8=A=0)	out	(CBR),a			;MMU Common Base Register = 0	out	(39h),a			;MMU Bank Base Register = 0	ld	a,88h			;7/3 = 1  CA3/BA3 Common Area @ 0x8000					;6/2 = 0  CA2/BA2					;5/1 = 0  CA1/BA1					;4/0 = 0  CA0/BA0	out0	(3ah),a			;MMU Common/Bank Area Register	eject;----------------------------------------------------------------------------;	Hardware is now programmed as intended;	All patches in table have been applied - turn interrupts back on;----------------------------------------------------------------------------	ei	;------------------------------------------------------------DEBUG:	ld	hl,(oldhigh)		;<3>Get where it was when we moved it	ld	a,h			;<3>or did we move it?	or	l			;<3>	jr	z,nomov2		;<3>Dont change it	ld	b,0			;<3>	ldos	@high			;<3>nomov2:	ld	a,(quiet)		;Should we say we are done?	or	a	jr	nz,skip2	ld	hl,WORKED		;Report all done	ldos	@dsplyskip2:	ld	hl,(nxtcmd)		;<5>	ld	a,(hl)			;See if it was empty	cp	0dh			;Anything there?	jr	z,plexit		;@cmndi should handle this	ld	a,(quiet)		;Get noise signal	or	a	jr	z,docmd			;Run normally	ld	c,27			;Make up for line SYS1/SYS will	ldos	@dsp			;waste so screen will matchdocmd:	ldos	@cmndi			;Pass tailings as next command.plexit:	ld	hl,0			;No command, just exit	ldos	@exit;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------;	Handle error conditions as well as possible;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------bad1:	ld	hl,BAD1MSG	jr	ab1bad2:	ld	hl,BAD2MSGab1:	ldos	@dsply	ldos	@abort	eject;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------;	Patch records are of the form:;	defw	address 	address to be patched;	defb	n		length of patch;	code 			Patch of 1 or more bytes, up to 255 per patch;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------opatches:patcha:	equ	206h			;PATCH HA (Original HOUDE)	defw	patcha			;"fix lowmem pointer"	defb	patcha_e-patcha	setloc	patchar_newfre:equ	$	defw	0000h			;New address is patched in at runtimepatcha_e:	resloca_newfre:equ	$-(patcha_e-r_newfre);----------------------------------------------------------------------------patchb:	equ	06c9h	defw	patchb			;PATCH HB & HC (Original HOUDE)					;PATCH C2  (Modified by M. A. D.					;	    Software.)	defb	patchb_e-patchb		;B=="new @MUL16 svc'	setloc	patchb			;C=="TASKER patch1. end of old @mul16"	ld	d,a	ld	e,l	ld	l,a	defb	0edh,06ch		;mlt	hl	defb	0edh,05ch		;mlt	de	ld	a,e	ld	e,d	ld	d,0	add	hl,de	ret	defb	0edh,028h,CBR		;in0	l,(38h)	ex	(sp),hl	push	hl	xor	a	out	(CBR),a			;<2>	ld	hl,OPREG$	retpatchb_e:	resloc;----------------------------------------------------------------------------	eject	iff	newpatchpatchd:	equ	0877h			;PATCH HD (original HOUDE)	defw	patchd			;"@BANK beginning, XBUR$ @0x87b"	defb	patchd_e-patchd	setloc	patchd	ld	a,c			;Copy bank into A (not really needed)r_baddr:equ	$+1	jp	0			;Jump to patch (in lowram driver form)XBUR$	defb	0			;XBUR$patchd_e:	resloca_baddr:equ	$-(patchd_e-r_baddr)	elsepatchd:	equ	0877h			;PATCH D2, (Copyright 1990 M. A. D.	defw	patchd			;<2>	    Software.)	defb	patchd_e-patchd		;<2>	setloc	patchd			;<2>;----------------------------------------------------------------------------;	NewBank - Replaces the existing @BANK SVC with one capable of;		  handling the extra RAM on the XLR8er adapter.;		  Copyright 1990   M. A. D. Software, All Rights Reserved.;<2>	This code was added in Edit 2;----------------------------------------------------------------------------	ld	a,b			;Get the command	cp	4			;Test for commands 0-3	jr	c,legal			;Yes it is;	Handle B = 4 and errors	ld	a,(LBANK$)		;Get current bank setting	ret	z			;Return Z and bank setting for code 4;	Command or bank number was no goodperr:	jp	LPERR			;Jump to Parameter Error Coder_baw:	defw	0			;Bank Access Word (replaces BUR$)					;As structured, this driver can					;handle up to 16 banks.					;Banks 0 - 2 are handled via 0x84,					;banks 3 - n are handled via 64180legal:	ld	a,c			;Get bank number	and	7fh			;Clear bit 7	cp	maxbanks+1		;Is bank number in range?	jr	nc,perr			;Nope;	Here the command code and bank number are valid;	Force the bank number into high bits - seems everyone wants them;	up there anyway.   Not entirely moved here	rrca				;3-0       -> 2-0 & 7     0	rrca				;2-0 & 7   -> 1-0 & 7-6   1	rrca				;1-0 & 7-6 ->   0 & 7-5   2	dec	b	jp	m,select		;Select Bank c	( B == 0 )	eject;	The following code handles the bank arbitration commands;	for both existing and new banks of RAM.;	Assumption - the target system has 128K base and 256K extended RAM	ld	c,86h			;Second byte of RES n,(HL) opcode	jr	z,reset			;Reset Bank-In-Use flag  ( B == 1 )	ld	c,46h			;Second byte of BIT n,(HL) opcode	dec	b	jr	z,test			;Test Bank-In-Use flag  ( B == 2 );	Fall into Set Bank-In-Use flag  ( B == 3 )	ld	b,a			;Save bank requested	call	test			;Test if in use already	ret	nz			;Abort if the bank is already in use	ld	a,b			;Get the bank number requested	ld	c,0c6h			;Second byte of SET n,(HL) opcodereset:	test:	push	hl			;Save HL	ld	hl,r_baw		;Point at Bank Allocation Word LSB	rrca				;  0 & 7-5 ->       7-4   3	jr	nc,lowbk		;Process low bank	inc	hl			;Bump pointer to MSBlowbk:	rrca				;      7-4 ->       6-3	and	38h			;Mask out bits 5-3 (bit to test)	or	c			;Or in rest of opcode	ld	(patch),a		;Patch in LSB	xor	a			;Set flags in case of SET or RES op	ld	a,8			;Prepare Device Not Availablepatch:	equ	$+1	bit	0,(hl)			;Reset, Set, or Test bit					;*** SELF-MODIFIED CODE ***	pop	hl	ret				;Return result;	Enable the requested bankselect:					;B=0	push	hl			;Save HL	ld	hl,8005h		;Determine if stack is in the bank	add	hl,sp			;region (or shortly will be)	pop	hl	jr	c,perr			;Don't allow the switch	rrca				;  0 & 7-5 ->       7-4   3	cp	30h			;Determine which hardware shouldr_baddr:equ	$+1			;(The addr will be patched in at r/t)	jp	nc,0			;handle the job  (Bits are in hi nib)	eject;	Here the old hardware is to handle the task.  Force the new RAM;	system into bank 0. Otherwise its mapping will override our settings.;<3>	This code maintains compatibility with the bank numbering definition;<3>	used by TRSDOS 6 / LS-DOS 6.  Edit 2 had the hardware assignment of;<3>	banks 1 & 2 swapped to allow this replacement module to fit.  Edit 3;<3>	provided enough space to provide the compatible bank-mapping.	or	a			;<3>Is it 0? then leave it.  00 to 00	jr	z,nofud			;<3>No fudge	add	a,10h			;<3>10 to 20, 20 to 30nofud:					;<3>	ld	b,a			;Save bit mask	ld	a,(OPREG$)		;P/u current memory	and	08fh			;configuration &	or	b			;mask off old &	ld	(OPREG$),a		;merge the new	out	(OPREGR),a		;Switch the hardware	xor	a			;Get a zero	out	(CBR),a			;Set CBR to zero (A15-A8=A=0)					;Disable mapping by MMUupdbank:				;Entry from new hardware section	ld	a,(LBANK$)		;Get old bank #	ld	b,a			;	& save it	ld	a,c			;Pick up new bank #	and	7fh			;Strip any bit-7	ld	(LBANK$),a		; & save new bank #	xor	c			;Keep bit-7	or	b			;Merge in new bank #	ld	c,a			;  & replace into C	cp	a			;<3>Set Z flag	rlca				;<3>Set carry based on bit 7	ld	b,0			;<3>Set up init for later invoc	ret	nc			;<3>Dont transfer to new bank					;<3>if bit 7 (in A) is non-zero	ex	(sp),hl			;Exchange RET with new	ret				;All done (Z flag still set)patchd_e:	resloca_baddr:equ	$-(patchd_e-r_baddr)a_baw:	equ	$-(patchd_e-r_baw)	endif;----------------------------------------------------------------------------	ejectpatche:	equ	0b9ah			;PATCH HE (original HOUDE)	defw	patche			;"@VDCTL jp to fix"	defb	patche_e-patche	setloc	patcher_vaddr:	defw	0000h			;Entry vector is patched in at rtimepatche_e:	resloca_vaddr:	equ	$-(patche_e-r_vaddr);----------------------------------------------------------------------------	ift	newpatchpatchf:	equ	0ddah			;PATCH F2, (Copyright 1990 M. A. D.	defw	patchf			;<2>	    Software.)	defb	patchf_e-patchf	setloc	patchfLINESIZ:equ	80			;<2>80 characters per line	push	hl			;<2>Save callers HL	ld	e,l			;<2>Save row	ld	l,LINESIZ		;<2>80 columns per line	defb	0edh,06ch		;<2>MLT	HL					;<2>Multiply rows * line size	ld	d,0f8h			;<2>Add in base address	add	hl,de			;<2>Add line offset	ex	de,hl			;<2>Move to DE	pop	hl			;<2>Restore HL	xor	a			;<2>Set Z flag	ret				;<2>Exit;<2>	End of @VDCTL modifications (jumped from dummy driver)vidfinish:	ex	(sp),hl			;Get back old HL (H=A, L=F)	defb	0edh,021h,CBR		;out0	(CBR),h	;Reset MMU settings	pop	hl			;Restore HL	retpatchf_e:	resloc	elsepatchf:	equ	0ddfh			;PATCH HF (original HOUDE)	defw	patchf			;"ROWCOL 2 ADDR multiply"	defb	patchf_e-patchf	setloc	patchf	ld	l,50h	defb	0edh,06ch		;mlt	hl	nop	nop	nop	noppatchf_e:	resloc	endif;----------------------------------------------------------------------------patchg:	equ	0f26h			;PATCH HG (original HOUDE)	defw	patchg			;"change delay in FDC driver"	defb	patchg_e-patchg	setloc	patchg	defb	024hpatchg_e:	resloc;----------------------------------------------------------------------------	eject@_VDCTL:equ	0d42h			;Entry point into video driver	iff	newpatche087e:	equ	087eh			;<5>Entry point back into @bankupdbank:equ	08dbh			;<5>Entry point back into @bank;e08db:	equ	08dbh			;Entry point back into @bankpatchh:	equ	0000h			;PATCH HH (original HOUDE)daddr:					;"add XLR8 module @BANK & @VDCTL"	defw	patchh			;Address is patched in at Rtime	defb	patchh_e-patchh	setloc	patchhloop:	jr	loopr_endmod:	defw	0r_modname:	defb	04	defm	'XLR8'r_bentry:and	7fh			;Strip possible bit 7	cp	0bh			;Bank out of range?	jr	nc,perr	sub	3			;Determine if old or new memory	jr	nc,newiron		;Request concerns new RAM	xor	a			;Access old Banks	out0	(CBR),a			;Reset MMU	ld	a,c			;Reload bank number	and	7fh			;Strip possible bit 7	jp	e087e			;Go back to old bank manager;	This code handles the new drivernewiron:	push	hl			;Save callers HL	inc	b	dec	b	jr	z,select		;Select bank	       (B==0)	ld	l,a	inc	l	ld	a,80hlp1:	rlca				;Build bit mask based on bank #	dec	l	jr	nz,lp1	eject	ld	hl,XBUR$		;	dec	b	jr	z,reset			;Reset Bank In Use Bit (B==1)	dec	b	jr	z,test			;Test Bank In Use Bit  (B==2)	dec	b	jr	z,set			;Set Bank In Use Bit   (B==3)	dec	b	ld	a,(LBANK$)		;	pop	hl			;Restore HL	ret	z			;Return current bank # (B==4)perr:	ld	a,2bh			;Load Parameter Error	or	a			;Set NZ	ret				;Exitset:	defb	0edh,34h		;tst	(hl) (64180 only)	jr	nz,naerr	or	(hl)	jr	updbitsreset:	cpl				;	and	(hl)updbits:ld	(hl),a	xor	a			;Set Z for caller	pop	hl	ret				;Exittest:	and	(hl)			;naerr:	ld	a,8			;Load Device Not Available Error	pop	hl	retselect:	ld	hl,8005h		;Check if stack is in upper	add	hl,sp			;Bank area	pop	hl			;Reset HL	jr	c,perr			;Error if > x'7ffe'		rlca	rlca	rlca	add	a,38h	out0	(CBR),a			;Set new bank	jp	updbank			;<3>Jump back into old driver	eject;	Additional code to @VDCTLr_ventry:in0	a,(CBR)			;defb	0edh,38h,38h	or	a			;Are we in an upper bank?	jp	z,@_VDCTL		;No, do nothing special	push	af			;Save video setting	xor	a			;Set to zero	out0	(CBR),a			;defb	0edh,39h,38h	call	0d42h			;Perform video	ex	(sp),hl			;Get bank setting	defb	0edh,21h,CBR		;out0	(38h),h	pop	hl			;Restore HL	retpatchh_e:	resloc	elsepatchh:	equ	0000h			;PATCH H2, (Copyright 1990 M. A. D.daddr:					;	    Software.)	defw	patchh			;Address is patched in at Rtime	defb	patchh_e-patchh	setloc	patchh;----------------------------------------------------------------------------;	NewDrvr - Contains the overflow code from the @BANK SVC modifications;		  as well as the overflow from the @VDCTL changes.;		  Copyright 1990   M. A. D. Software, All Rights Reserved.;<2>	This code was added in Edit 2loop:	jr	loopr_endmod:	defw	0			;Start of next driver addressr_modname:	defb	2			;Was 4 but name changed	defm	'XL'			;Was 'XL8R' but I want the RAM!;	This handles the new hardware bank management;	Now uses 9 bytes - was 91 bytes, or 90% smallerr_bentry:	rrca				;Move bits to 5-3	add	a,20h			;Combine bank with memory base					;Program MMU.  This overrides the					;settings implemented off-chip on					;main logic so they don't need setting	out0	CBR,a	jp	updbank			;Update bank setting	eject;	This code makes sure the MMU is disabled when we attempt to;	open the video/keyboard bank.;	Now uses 17 bytes - was 21 bytesr_ventry:	in0	a,(CBR)			;Is MMU bank non-zero?	or	a	jp	z,@_VDCTL		;Already zero, take no action	push	af			;Save that setting	xor	a			;Get a zero	out	(CBR),a			;Disable MMU so video/key bank will					;select by making base address 0					;(A8-A15=A=0)	call	@_VDCTL			;Perform requested action	jp	vidfinish		;<2>Use 6 bytes of space back in $DOpatchh_e:	resloc	endifa_modname:equ	$-(patchh_e-r_modname)a_endmod:equ	$-(patchh_e-r_endmod)o_bentry:equ	r_bentry-patchho_ventry:equ	r_ventry-patchhDRVSIZ:	equ	patchh_e-patchh;----------------------------------------------------------------------------	eject;----------------------------------------------------------------------------;	SYS0 patches follow;----------------------------------------------------------------------------patchi:	equ	190ah			;PATCH HI (original HOUDE)	defw	patchi			;"new @MUL8 svc"	defb	patchi_e-patchi	setloc	patchi	ld	d,a	defb	0edh,05ch	ld	a,e	retpatchi_e:	resloc;----------------------------------------------------------------------------patchj:	equ	190fh			;PATCH HJ (original HOUDE)	defw	patchj			;"TASKER patch2. end of old @MUL8"	defb	patchj_e-patchj	setloc	patchj	defb	0edh,029h,CBR		;	ld	a,h	ld	(0202h),a	retpatchj_e:	resloc;----------------------------------------------------------------------------patchk:	equ	1a16h			;PATCH HK (original HOUDE)	defw	patchk			;"fix to call modified @bank	defb	patchk_e-patchk		; instead of SVC (disk I/O)"	setloc	patchk		call	patchd			;<3>0877hpatchk_e:	resloc;----------------------------------------------------------------------------	ejectpatchl:	equ	1c11h			;PATCH HL (original HOUDE)	defw	patchl			;"tasker (beginning)"	defb	patchl_e-patchl	setloc	patchl	ld	h,a	call	06d6hpatchl_e:	resloc;----------------------------------------------------------------------------patchm:	equ	1c3ch			;PATCH HM (original HOUDE)	defw	patchm			;"tasker (end)"	defb	patchm_e-patchm	setloc	patchm	pop	hl	call	190fhpatchm_e:	resloc;----------------------------------------------------------------------------	defw	0			;END OF PATCHES	defb	0			;END OF PATCHES	eject;----------------------------------------------------------------------------;	Utility messages and data;----------------------------------------------------------------------------BAD1MSG:defm	'?Low memory has gone negative! - Check system consistency.'	defb	0dhBAD2MSG:defm	'?Not enough low-memory for XLR8er patches.'	defm	'  Needs 35 bytes.'	defb	0dhBAD3MSG:defm	'?XLR8er BOOT and SYS0 patches already installed.'	defb	0dhBAD4MSG:defm	'?This system does not have a HD64180 processor.'	defb	0dh	ejectBAD5MSG:defm	'?The base system does not have 128K of RAM.'	;<2>	defb	0dh			;<2>USAGE:defm	'?Usage:  XLR8SET [-qs1?h] [[-m] [-b "progname"]] '	defm	'[progname....]'	defb	0ah	defm	'Options are: (? or h displays this message)'	defb	0ah	defm	'-q   Only display error messages'	defb	0ah	defm	'-s   Do not adjust Z180 operating speed'	defb	0ah	defm	'-1   System only has 128K of RAM'	defb	0ah	defm	'-m   Don''t change HIGH$ while -b commands are executed'	defb	0ah	defm	'-b "program"'	defb	0ah	defm	'     Execute "program" before applying the Z180 patches'	defb	0dhBAD8MSG:defm	'?Patches are designed for use on LS-DOS 6.3.0 and 6.3.1';<3>	defm	' only.'		;<3>	defb	0dh			;<3>	ejectWORKED:	defm	'Patches installed successfully.'	defb	0dhnxtcmd:	defw	0			;<5>inoption:defb	0			;<5>quiet:	defb	0slow:	defb	0			;<2>lockmem:defb	0			;<3>oldhigh:defw	0			;<3>Old High$ valuetmpname:defb	9%0ourbuf:	defb	85%0			;<2>Store command line here	end	begin			;